25 SUBTITLE 12. MARYLAND ASSISTIVE TECHNOLOGY PROGRAM.
26 7–1201.
27 (A) IN THIS SUBTITLE THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
28 INDICATED.
29 (B) “ASSISTIVE TECHNOLOGY DEVICE” MEANS ANY ITEM, PIECE OF
30 EQUIPMENT, OR PRODUCT SYSTEM, WHETHER ACQUIRED COMMERCIALLY,

HOUSE BILL 214 3
1 MODIFIED, OR CUSTOMIZED, THAT IS USED TO INCREASE, MAINTAIN, OR IMPROVE
2 FUNCTIONAL CAPABILITIES OF INDIVIDUALS WITH DISABILITIES.
3 (C) “ASSISTIVE TECHNOLOGY SERVICE” MEANS ANY SERVICE THAT ASSISTS
4 AN INDIVIDUAL WITH A DISABILITY IN THE SELECTION, ACQUISITION, OR USE OF AN
5 ASSISTIVE TECHNOLOGY DEVICE.
6 (D) “FUND” MEANS THE ASSISTIVE TECHNOLOGY SERVICES FUND.
7 (E) “PROGRAM” MEANS THE MARYLAND ASSISTIVE TECHNOLOGY
8 PROGRAM.
9 7–1202.
10 (A) THERE IS A MARYLAND ASSISTIVE TECHNOLOGY PROGRAM IN THE
11 DEPARTMENT.
12 (B) THE PURPOSE OF THE PROGRAM IS TO:
13 (1) INCREASE ACCESS TO ASSISTIVE TECHNOLOGY DEVICES AND
14 ASSISTIVE TECHNOLOGY SERVICES FOR INDIVIDUALS WITH DISABILITIES;
15 (2) SUPPORT THE STATE’S EFFORTS TO IMPROVE THE PROVISION OF
16 ASSISTIVE TECHNOLOGY TO INDIVIDUALS WITH DISABILITIES OF ALL AGES,
17 INCLUDING UNDERREPRESENTED POPULATIONS, THROUGH COMPREHENSIVE
18 STATEWIDE PROGRAMS OF TECHNOLOGY–RELATED ASSISTANCE;
19 (3) ENSURE STATEWIDE ACCESS TO ASSISTIVE TECHNOLOGY
20 LENDING LIBRARIES THAT ALLOW INDIVIDUALS WITH DISABILITIES AND THOSE
21 SUPPORTING INDIVIDUALS WITH DISABILITIES TO LEARN ABOUT, TRY, AND BORROW
22 ASSISTIVE TECHNOLOGY DEVICES THROUGH SHORT–TERM LOANS; AND
23 (4) IMPLEMENT ACTIVITIES REQUIRED BY FEDERAL GRANTS,
24 INCLUDING FUNDING AUTHORIZED UNDER THE FEDERAL 21ST CENTURY ASSISTIVE
25 TECHNOLOGY ACT.
26 (C) THE PROGRAM SHALL PROVIDE ACCESS TO OR CONDUCT ASSISTIVE
27 TECHNOLOGY SERVICES THAT INCLUDE ANY ACTIVITY DESCRIBED IN THE FEDERAL
28 21ST CENTURY ASSISTIVE TECHNOLOGY ACT.
29 7–1203.
30 (A) THERE IS AN ASSISTIVE TECHNOLOGY SERVICES FUND IN THE
31 DEPARTMENT.

4 HOUSE BILL 214
1 (B) THE PURPOSE OF THE FUND IS TO RECEIVE REVENUE FROM ASSISTIVE
2 TECHNOLOGY SERVICES PROVIDED BY THE PROGRAM, INCLUDING:
3 (1) ASSISTIVE TECHNOLOGY ASSESSMENTS;
4 (2) ASSISTIVE TECHNOLOGY TRAINING;
5 (3) DIGITAL ACCESSIBILITY TRAINING;
6 (4) DIGITAL ACCESSIBILITY WEBSITE EVALUATIONS; AND
7 (5) DIGITAL ACCESSIBILITY REMEDIATION SERVICES.
8 (C) THE SECRETARY, THROUGH THE PROGRAM, SHALL ADMINISTER THE
9 FUND.
10 (D) (1) THE FUND IS A SPECIAL, NONLAPSING FUND THAT IS NOT
11 SUBJECT TO § 7–302 OF THE STATE FINANCE AND PROCUREMENT ARTICLE.
12 (2) THE STATE TREASURER SHALL HOLD THE FUND SEPARATELY,
13 AND THE COMPTROLLER SHALL ACCOUNT FOR THE FUND.
14 (E) THE FUND CONSISTS OF:
15 (1) REVENUE DISTRIBUTED TO THE FUND UNDER SUBSECTION (B) OF
16 THIS SECTION;
17 (2) MONEY APPROPRIATED IN THE STATE BUDGET TO THE FUND;
18 (3) INTEREST EARNINGS; AND
19 (4) ANY OTHER MONEY FROM ANY OTHER SOURCE ACCEPTED FOR
20 THE BENEFIT OF THE FUND.
21 (F) THE FUND MAY BE USED ONLY TO SUPPORT THE OPERATIONS OF THE
22 PROGRAM, INCLUDING THE PURCHASE OF ASSISTIVE TECHNOLOGY DEVICES.
23 (G) (1) THE STATE TREASURER SHALL INVEST THE MONEY OF THE FUND
24 IN THE SAME MANNER AS OTHER STATE MONEY MAY BE INVESTED.
25 (2) ANY INTEREST EARNINGS OF THE FUND SHALL BE CREDITED TO
26 THE FUND.

